This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of Computational Linguistics (cs.CL) because it presents a tagger based on convolutional neural networks for natural language processing tasks such as part-of-speech tagging and morphological tagging. It is also likely to belong to the sub-category of Machine Learning (cs.LG) because it uses neural networks for learning and classification. Additionally, it could belong to the sub-categories of Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) because of the use of neural networks for learning and classification. Finally, it could also belong to the sub-category of Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition (cs.CV) because convolutional neural networks are commonly used in image processing tasks.
